review_blob:
Lovely hoppy homage to the Guinness stout brand. Light in colour and easily a 45 in IBU, this beer is a wonderful addition to the Guinness brand! Purchased a bottle at The Zoo in Osborne Village, Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Wonderfully hoppy with a light copper body. Light head that collapses slowly. Citrus and playful floral notes, I find similarities to earl grey tea in the finishing notes.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Copper colour, tan head. Smooth & earthy taste with lightly bitter finish. Ordered a pint at Shannon's in Winnipeg. Served with appropriate head, perfectly cold and from clean taps.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Granville Island English Bay Pale Ale

review_blob:
Perfect balance of beer and grapefruit flavour. A summer must have for any beer drinker. Good cold or at room temperature.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Wonderful, smooth porter with slight coconut finish. Would prefer a more prominent coconut flavour.

Very neutral and simple beer, good cold, but loses drinkability as temperature rises.
